Roles & Responsibilities
MNC in SG
Work-life balance
About Our Client
Our client is working on server platform/data center technologies.
Job Description
Responsibilities:

- Ensuring the baseline server standards of BIOS/UEFI and BMC meet the Data Center operational requirements;

- Performing verification and approval of BIOS/UEFI and BMC new versions from our server vendors;

- Participate in emergency responses for server firmware related incidents in the Data Centers;

- Serve as the primary escalation point for end users regarding issues within the OS, coordinating across all internal teams to ensure issue resolution is completed promptly;

- Developing familiarity with Data Centers server firmwares to improve stability to meet business goals;
The Successful Applicant
Qualifications
- Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering or related majors;
- Experiences in server firmware development or in similar fields;
- Familiar with server hardware architecture, RAS, PECI, or server secure boot;
- Familiar with the principle or architecture either in BIOS/UEFI or BMC;
- Possesses solid trouble-shooting and problem solving skills in the server hardware layer;
What's on Offer
Competitive salary

