About the team
The System Technologies and Engineering team is looking for experienced Operation System Software Engineer to build the Operating System (OS) image automation system within the Data Center. This individual will work with the global team to improve the existing image build system, enhance the automation level, and publish the OS image to be ready for bare metal servers or cloud servers to install or deploy.

Responsibilities:
- Maintaining the Linux Based operating system image automated build system;
- Improving the operating system to meet the changing requirements;
- Reviewing component changes to ensure modified packages could be delivered successfully;
- Performing root-cause analysis to identify system issues or faults and recommending solutions to resolve them;
- Write and maintain programmable code outlined in technical instructions and specifications for software applications and operating systems.

Qualifications:
- Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering or related majors;
- Proficient with Linux OS distribution image builds such as Debian, Fedora, OpenSuSE, or similiar;
- Proficient with Linux package management software, such as dpkg, rpm, yum, dnf, or similar;
- Proficient with CI/CD, SCM, git, autoconf, automake, etc;
- Proficient in any programming such as C/C++, Java, Python, or Golang;

